Raptors 99, SuperSonics 97
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SEATTLE(AP) -- Vince Carter scored 13 of his game-high 34 points in the first
quarter as the Toronto Raptors raced to a 17-point lead and held off the
SuperSonics 99-97 Sunday for their first win in Seattle. Tracy McGrady added 19
points and Doug Christie 13 as the Raptors got back on track after seeing their
franchise-high seven-game winning streak snapped Friday at Sacramento.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
