<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Johnny Newman came off the bench to score a
season-high 26 points and lead the New Jersey Nets past the Orlando Magic 129-91
Sunday night for their third straight victory. The Nets ended Orlando's winning
streak at three and moved within three games of the Magic and the Milwaukee
Bucks for the final playoff spot in the Eastern Conference. Darrell Armstrong
led the Magic with 15.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Duke Among Top Seeds in NCAA Tournament
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Duke and Michigan State were seeded No. 1 for the second
straight year in the NCAA tournament and will be joined by the Pac-10's Stanford
and Arizona as the top teams. Cincinnati, which had been ranked No. 1 in the AP
poll for 12 weeks but lost center Kenyon Martin to a broken leg last week, was
seeded second as the 64-team field was announced tonight.
</P>
