<HEADLINE> Dow Drops 140; Nasdaq Tumbles 184  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 140
points in today's early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 2-1 over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 184 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down 16 points.
</P>
<P>
   It looks like the recent volatility in stock prices still has a
ways to go.
</P>
<P>
   Today's sharp selling pressure follows steep declines for
virtually all the major overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
   The only item of a fundamental nature for traders was word that
Japan's economy was in worse shape than expected.
</P>
<P>
   On Wall Street, some analysts say the sentiment has turned so
decidedly against the old-line blue-chip stocks that bargain
hunters may soon be able to find some real value in the market amid
the beaten-down issues.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
