<HEADLINE> Chelsea Clinton Going to Asia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- While her mom stays home to campaign, Chelsea
Clinton will accompany her dad, President Clinton, to India,
Bangladesh and Pakistan on a trip beginning Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   It will be Chelsea's second trip to South Asia. She went to
India and Pakistan with her mother, Hillary Rodham Clinton, on a
goodwill visit in April 1995. This time, the first lady will remain
behind to run for the Senate in New York. Chelsea will have time
off for spring break at Stanford University.
</P>
<P>
   White House press secretary Joe Lockhart said Chelsea would not
be the first lady's stand-in at official events.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't know what she'll do but she'll serve the role she
normally serves as the president's daughter,'' Lockhart said.
</P>
