<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greek Police Detain Immigrants  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATHENS, Greece (AP) -- Police detained more than 350 Iraqi
Kurdish and African illegal immigrants found on a deserted beach on
Chios Island, located in the Aegean Sea across from Turkey, the
Merchant Marine Ministry said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   A boat dropped the group off late Sunday on the island, where
they were found by a coast guard patrol. They were taken to a
nearby town and given food and shelter.
</P>
<P>
   Tens of thousands from Asia and Eastern Europe sneak into the
country each year, hoping to make their way to Greece or other
European Union countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
