<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in Texas Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BRUNI, Texas (AP) -- A car and a tanker-truck collided head-on in
south Texas Monday, killing all seven men in the car, authorities
said.
</P>
<P>
   The accident took place on a state highway about 40 miles east
of Laredo, said Webb County Justice of the Peace Alfredo Garcia.
</P>
<P>
   The men were traveling eastbound in a Chevrolet Cavalier that
collided with the westbound 18-wheeler, whose driver was taken to
Mercy Regional Medical Center in Laredo, he said. A hospital
spokeswoman said the driver was treated and released.
</P>
<P>
   ''We don't know if the car lost control or the truck lost
control,'' Garcia said. ''We'll have to wait and see what
happened.''
</P>
<P>
   The accident was reported at 12:43 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   The victims appeared to be between the ages of 20 and 39, Garcia
said. It was not immediately known if they were related.
</P>
<P>
   ''I've been to several accidents and this is the worst one I've
seen,'' Garcia said. ''Believe me, it's a total mess.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
