<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-13 19:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Covering Meant for Pope Collapses  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JERUSALEM (AP) -- Part of a covering meant to protect the pope
from the sun collapsed Monday on the stage where he is to conduct a
huge open-air Mass near the Sea of Galilee next week, an Israeli
official said.
</P>
<P>
   John Paul II is to address an estimated 100,000 worshippers from
that stage on March 24.
</P>
<P>
   Father Antonio, a Catholic Church representative at Korazim,
where the stage has been built, said in a telephone interview that
''only a cable snapped.''
</P>
<P>
   A spokesman for the Israel Electric Corporation, however, said
the center pole supporting the roof buckled, and the roof collapsed
onto the stage.
</P>
<P>
   The government-owned electric company has overall responsibility
for preparing the site, but the church chose to engage a private
Israeli contractor to build the stage, said the spokesman, Dedi
Golan.
</P>
<P>
   In the wake of the collapse, the church asked the electric
company to repair the center-pole and the roof, Golan said.
</P>
<P>
   The Mass is to be held on the Mount of the Beatitudes, the
Galilee hilltop where Jesus is believed to have delivered the
sermon beginning ''Blessed are the poor in spirit.'' The hill
overlooks the Sea of Galilee and the sites where tradition says
Jesus walked on water and performed the Miracle of the Loaves and
Fish.
</P>
<P>
   The event is expected to be a highlight of the pontiff's Holy
Land visit March 21-26.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-03-13-00 1914 </TRAILER>
