<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Murder Suspect Sought in Maryland  </HEADLINE>
By ALEX DOMINGUEZ, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   BALTIMORE (AP) -- A police search of wooded areas Monday failed
to flush out the man suspected of killing four people and
kidnapping his girlfriend during a rampage last week.
</P>
<P>
   A line of 60 police officers, spaced about 100 yards apart,
marched through two state parks about 15 miles from Baltimore in
hopes of finding Joseph Palczynski.
</P>
<P>
   ''Nothing and no one has been found,'' said police spokesman
Bill Toohey. Police would not say what led them to the parks, but
they say Palczynski obtained outdoor equipment over the past week.
</P>
<P>
   Police say Palczynski, 31, shot and killed three people March 7
while kidnapping his estranged girlfriend, and then shot a fourth
person the next day as he tried to steal a car. The girlfriend
escaped Wednesday night and Palczynski disappeared.
</P>
<P>
   He resurfaced in Virginia, stealing guns and a van and forcing a
man to drive him back to Baltimore over the weekend, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Also Monday, a woman accused of buying weapons for Palczynski
was ordered held in federal custody for a mental exam.
</P>
<P>
   Constance Waugh, 48, was arrested Friday and charged with lying
on a federal form by saying she, not Palczynski, planned to use the
weapons, federal officials said.
</P>
<P>
   If convicted, she faces up to 10 years for the so-called ''straw
purchases,'' said Mike Campbell of the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco
and Firearms.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
