<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sacramento St. Hoops Coach Quits  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Sacramento State basketball coach Tom
Abatemarco resigned Monday, a week after the Hornets finished the
season 9-18.
</P>
<P>
   In a letter on university letterhead, received by news
organizations Monday, Abatemarco wrote that ''due to personal
reasons, I will be unable to continue as head basketball coach, and
am, therefore, resigning effective immediately.''
</P>
<P>
   Neither Abatemarco nor the university officials responded to
telephone messages left Monday afternoon seeking comment.
</P>
<P>
   Abatemarco had been under pressure because of reports of
strained relations with some of his players. Fourteen players left
the program during Abatemarco's three-year tenure.
</P>
<P>
   Athletic director Debby Colberg said earlier this month that she
would evaluate Abatemarco, 48, who was paid $76,596 a year.
</P>
<P>
   In 1997, Abatemarco inherited a woeful program that had gone
20-112 the previous five years. After going 1-25 in his first
season, Abatemarco led the Hornets to a 3-23 mark in 1998-99.
</P>
</TEXT>
