<HEADLINE> 6 Dogs Kill Brazilian Girl  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) -- Six guard dogs killed a 4-year-old girl
and injured her sister and their mother as they returned home late
from church, police and news reports said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The incident occurred Sunday night on a small farm in
Carapicuiba, a rural district on the outskirts of Sao Paulo, where
the mother and the children's father live and work as caretakers,
police said.
</P>
<P>
   Police inspector Fernando Cesar Costa de Oliveira said the dogs,
all Rottweillers, were apparently set loose earlier in the day by
the owner of the farm to guard the property.
</P>
<P>
   The victim suffered bite wounds to the face and died
immediately, Oliveira said. Her 3-year-old sister was rushed to a
hospital in serious condition. The mother was treated for less
serious bites she received trying to protect the girls.
</P>
<P>
   The three were attacked in the yard as they returned home from
church, local television reported.
</P>
<P>
   It was not clear if the owner would be charged in the incident.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's really tragic what happened,'' said Oliveira. ''There
should have been some way of controlling the dogs when someone
arrived.''
</P>
</TEXT>
